title: The following functions compute the area under the curve for a given distribution They are used to find p-values of a hypothesis test. T.DIST — p-value for a lower tailed t-test T.DIST.2T — p-value for a two-tailed t-test T.DIST.RT — p-value for an upper tailed t-test NORM.DIST — left area under normal curve up to an x-limit NORM.S.DIST — left area under normal curve up to a z-limit F.DIST — p-value for a lower tailed F-test F.DIST.RT
